By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The leadership of the All Progressives Congress will meet with the party’s senators-elect and members of the House of Representatives-elect on Monday. The meeting, which is scheduled to be held at the State House Banquet Hall, Abuja, will start at 2pm. According to an invitation signed by the National Secretary of the party, Iyiola Omisore, senators-elect and members of House of Representatives-elect are to attend the meeting with their Independent National Electoral Commission Certificates of Return. The invitation read in part, “This is to inform all Senators-Elect and members of the House of Representatives-Elect of the All Progressives Congress (APC), that they are invited to a parley with the Party’s National Leadership.“The meeting which will be attended by the President-Elect and Vice President-Elect, will be held at the State House Banquet Hall, Aso Rock Villa, Abuja. “Senators/House of Representatives-Elect must come to the meeting with their Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) Certificate of Return and must come alone. “The meeting is strictly on invitation.” It added that, “All invited guests are expected to arrive early to allow for screening and be seated before 12noon.”